UI_visible_response: The #MeToo movement is an awareness movement centered around the issue of sexual harassment and sexual abuse, particularly of women in the workplace, which grew to prominence in 20172. The movement was originally founded in 2006 by Tarana Burke to support survivors of sexual violence, particularly young women of color from low-wealth communities3.
